  "prompt": "Why was MM kalburgi killed?",
  "response": "MM Kalburgi, a prominent Kannada scholar and rationalist, was killed on August 30, 2015, near his home in Dharwad, Karnataka. He was shot dead by unidentified gunmen while he was returning home after attending a literary event. \n\nKalburgi was known for his critical views on certain religious practices and superstitions, particularly within Hinduism. He had been a vocal critic of idol worship and had made controversial statements about religious rituals that had angered some conservative religious groups. His academic work and rationalist stance had earned him both respect and criticism.\n\nBefore his murder, Kalburgi had received multiple threats from right-wing religious groups who were offended by his academic writings and public statements challenging religious orthodoxies. While the exact perpetrators were not immediately identified, his killing was seen as part of a pattern of attacks on rationalists and free thinkers in India.\n\nHis murder was part of a series of killings of rationalists and activists in India, including Narendra Dabholkar and Govind Pansare, which raised significant concerns about freedom of expression and growing intolerance towards critical thinking.\n\nThe investigation into his murder has been complex, with multiple theories but no definitive conclusive resolution as of now.",
